<p>I have a notifications dropdown in my AngularJS application. I want to call a function within the function that open the dropdown. Here is what I mean: </p>  <pre><code>$scope.showNotif = false;      $scope.toggleNotifDropdown = function(event) {         $scope.showNotif = !$scope.showNotif;          readNotifications = function() {             NotificationService.readNotifs().then(                 function(success) {                     console.log("Notifications read!");                 },                 function(errors) {                     console.log("Something wrong happened.");                 }             );         };          if($scope.showNotif) {             $document.bind('click', $scope.globalNotifClose);         } else {             $document.unbind('click', $scope.globalNotifClose);         }          event.stopPropagation();     }; </code></pre>  <p>The notifications dropdown works perfectly, I just can't get that function readNotifications() to work for me. Any suggestions would be great! Thanks!</p>